Hey @romani Can you just confirm that this is what you want?
This is the default config with set of examples I will add more to it and do the changes accordingly
class Test {
    public Test(){} // 2 violations , '{' is not followed and preceded by whitespace.
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        if (foo) { // ok
            // body
        }
        else{ // violation
            // body
        }
        for (int i = 1; i &gt; 1; i++) {} // 2 violations ,
                                            // '{' is not followed and preceded by whitespace.
        Runnable noop = () -&gt; {}; // 2 violations ,
                                        // '{' is not followed and preceded by whitespace.
    }
}

Now if i set a config with allowEmptyConstructors = true my example should look like this
class Test {
    public Test(){} // ok
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        if (foo) { // ok
            // body
        }
        else{ // violation
            // body
        }
        for (int i = 1; i &gt; 1; i++) {} // 2 violations ,
                                            // '{' is not followed and preceded by whitespace.
        Runnable noop = () -&gt; {}; // 2 violations ,
                                        // '{' is not followed and preceded by whitespace.
    }
}

So, you basically, want me to give examples for the default config, and the complement of it as well (i.e. for default: I give an example, and provide another similar example for something that's not a default ), is that right?
Is that all that you want me to do?

please do this all others that are ignored by default.

And this was the only example of ignoreEnhancedForColon which was ignored

@romani please check this one i added the for loop in the default config too where ignoreEnhancedForColon is true and made a config where ignoreEnhancedForColon is false with an example
And i think all the examples are covered, please tell me if I miss something else
Sorry for the trouble

